@startuml
!define RECTANGLE class

title Lyrics Sentiment Classification - Deployment and Control Flow

actor User
participant "React\nFrontend" as Frontend
participant "FastAPI\nBackend" as Backend
participant "Elasticsearch\nDatabase" as ES
participant "LyricsGenius\nAPI" as Genius
participant "CNN Model\nService" as CNN
database "Model Variables\n(variables.index)" as ModelDB

== System Deployment ==
note over Frontend, ModelDB
    Docker Compose orchestrates all services
end note

activate Frontend
activate Backend
activate ES
activate CNN

ES -> ES: startup.sh executes
ES -> ES: create_load_save_es_index.py
ES -> ES: Load lyrics from CSV/JSON
ES -> ES: Index created and populated

CNN -> ModelDB: Load trained model\nvariables
activate ModelDB
ModelDB --> CNN: Model parameters loaded
deactivate ModelDB

== User Query Flow ==
User -> Frontend: Enter song and artist
activate Frontend
Frontend -> Backend: POST /classify\n{song, artist}
activate Backend

Backend -> ES: Search for song\nby title and artist
activate ES
ES --> Backend: Check if exists
deactivate ES

alt Song found in Elasticsearch
    Backend -> Backend: Retrieve cached lyrics\nand mood
else Song not found
    Backend -> Genius: GET /search\n{song, artist}
    activate Genius
    Genius --> Backend: Return lyrics
    deactivate Genius

    Backend -> Backend: Preprocess lyrics\n(utils.py)
    Backend -> Backend: Normalize text
    Backend -> Backend: Tokenize
    Backend -> Backend: Remove stop words

    Backend -> CNN: Classify mood\n(preprocessed lyrics)
    activate CNN
    CNN -> CNN: Convert to embeddings
    CNN -> CNN: CNN inference
    CNN --> Backend: Mood classification
    deactivate CNN

    Backend -> ES: Index new song\n{lyrics, mood}
    activate ES
    ES --> Backend: Document indexed
    deactivate ES
end

== Similar Songs Recommendation ==
Backend -> ES: Query similar songs\nby mood
activate ES
ES --> Backend: Retrieve candidate songs
deactivate ES

Backend -> Backend: Calculate TF-IDF vectors
Backend -> Backend: Compute cosine similarity
Backend -> Backend: Rank similar songs

Backend --> Frontend: Return results\n{mood, similar songs}
deactivate Backend

Frontend -> Frontend: Render results
Frontend --> User: Display mood and\nrecommendations
deactivate Frontend

== Data Exploration (Offline) ==
note over Backend, ModelDB
    Jupyter Notebooks perform:
    - Dataset exploration
    - Preprocessing analysis
    - Model training (TensorFlow/Keras)
    - Model evaluation
    Model saved to cnn_model_v3/
end note

@enduml
